From Warren Vonroeschlaub Subject Re Albert Sabin In article Bill Rawlins writes Since you have referred to the Messiah I assume you are referring to the New Please detail your complaints or e mail if you don't want to First century Greek is well known and well Have you considered Josephus the Jewish Historian who also wrote of Jesus In addition the four gospel accounts are very much in Bill I find it rather remarkable that you managed to zero in on what is probably the weakest What is probably the most convincing is the anti Christian literature put out by the Jewish councils in the second There are enormous quantities of detailed arguments against Christianity many of the arguments still being used Despite volumes of tracts attacking Christianity not one denies the existance of Jesus only of his I find this considerably more compelling than Josephus or the harmony of the gospels especially considering that Matthew and Luke probably used Mark as a source L Warren Kurt vonRoeschlaub o ' Iowa State University Math Department Carver Hall Ames IA J